  "prompt": "How much money do I owe my housemate?",
  "response": "Okay, to figure out how much you owe your housemate, I need some information. Please tell me about:\n\n*   **Rent:**\n    *   What's the total monthly rent for the place?\n    *   How do you and your housemate split the rent (e.g., 50/50, 60/40, or a specific dollar amount each)?\n    *   Are you behind on rent for any months? If so, for which months and how much each month?\n\n*   **Utilities:**\n    *   Which utilities do you share (e.g., electricity, gas, water, internet)?\n    *   How do you split the utility bills (e.g., 50/50, based on usage, etc.)?\n    *   For each utility, what was the total bill amount for the last few months, and what portion is your responsibility?\n    *   Are you behind on paying your share of any utility bills? If so, which ones and how much?\n\n*   **Other Shared Expenses:**\n    *   Do you share the cost of groceries, household supplies (e.g., cleaning products, toilet paper), or other items?\n    *   How do you split these expenses?\n    *   Do you owe your housemate money for any of these items? If so, what and how much?\n\n*   **Past Payments:**\n    *   When was the last time you paid your housemate?\n    *   How much did you pay them at that time?\n    *   What did that payment cover (e.g., rent for a specific month, utilities for a specific period, etc.)?\n\n*   **Any Other Agreements:**\n    *   Are there any other agreements between you and your housemate about expenses (e.g., one person pays for something in exchange for something else)?\n    *   Have you borrowed money from your housemate for any other reason?\n\nOnce I have this information, I can help you calculate how much you owe.\n\n**Example:**\n\nLet's say:\n\n*   Rent is $1500/month, split 50/50. You owe $750/month.\n*   You haven't paid rent for the last month.\n*   The electricity bill for last month was $100, split 50/50. You owe $50.\n*   You owe $25 for your share of groceries.\n\nThen you would owe: $750 (rent) + $50 (electricity) + $25 (groceries) = $825\n\n**Important Considerations:**\n\n*   **Communication:** The best way to resolve this is to talk to your housemate openly and honestly about the situation.\n*   **Records:** Keep track of all payments you make and any agreements you have with your housemate. This will help prevent misunderstandings in the future.\n*   **Fairness:** Make sure the way you're splitting expenses is fair to both of you. If something isn't working, be willing to discuss it and find a better solution.\n\nProvide me with the details, and I'll do my best to help you calculate the amount you owe.\n",
